<div class="header">
    <div class="icon"></div>
    <h2>Employees</h2>
    <span class="hint">Number of full-time equivalent employees</span>
    <input type="text" class="valueBox" />
    <span class="prompt">Please enter <br />how many employees you have</span>
    <div class="gauge "></div>
    <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="button medium runReport ">Run Report</a>
    <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="reportToggle"></a>
</div>
<div class="body ">
    <div class="loading">
        <p class="title">Employee Report</p>
        <img src="@Url.Content("~/content/images/Loading.gif")" alt="Loading" />
        <p class="message">Generating Report</p>
    </div>
    <div class="reportContainer ">
         <div class="reportContent noDataError">
            <p>There is no data available for this report with this industry and city</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reportContent">
            <h3>How you size up</h3>
            <p class="description">
                <div data-template="description">
                                In your industry, your business has more employees than 100% of businesses in your city, 
                27% of businesses in your county, 28% of businesses in your metro area, 37% of businesses 
                in your state, and 34% of businesses in the nation.
            


                @Html.Raw(ViewBag.Strings["Dashboard.Revenue.Description"])
                </div>
            </p>
            <div class="chart">
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="mapToggle" data-toggleText="View Variations by Geography">Hide Variations by Geography</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="chartToggle" data-toggleText="View Chart">View Data Table</a>
                <div class="container"></div>
            </div>
            <table class="table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td class="label">Business/Geography</td>
                        <td class="value">Value</td>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="container">
                    <tr data-template="tableRow">
                        <td class="name">{{name}}</td>
                        <td class="value">{{value}}</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
            <ul class="links">
                <li>
                    <a class="source" href="javascript:void(0);" data-toggleText="Hide">Source</a>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <div class="sourceContent " data-expandedClass="expanded">
                @Html.Raw(ViewBag.Strings["Dashboard.Revenue.Source"])
                 <p>Employee data for communities on SizeUp is aggregated from data on individual businesses,
                    which comes from hundreds of data sources including, but not limited to, IRS records,
                    county courthouse filings, Yellow Pages and White Pages, business publications,
                    the U.S. Postal Service, and corporate annual reports.
                </p>

            </div>
            <div class="map heatmap">
                <p class="title backdrop"></p>
                <div class="legend backdrop">
                    <ul class="legendContainer">
                        <li data-template="legendItem"><div class="block" data-override-style="background-color: {{color}};"></div><span class="range">{{label}}</span></li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="bottom backdrop"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="container"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="reportSidebar">
            <div class="section considerations collapsable">
                <h4>Considerations</h4>
                <p>Are you larger or smaller than the average business in your area?  You should be aware of the advantages
                    and disadvantages for either situation, and how to promote the advantages to your customers.
                </p>



                @Html.Raw(ViewBag.Strings["Dashboard.Revenue.Considerations"])


                <div class="question">
                    <span>Are you a <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="startup">startup</a> or an <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="established">established business</a>?</span>
                </div>
                <div class="startup answer collapsed hidden">
                    <h5>you are a startup</h5>
                    <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="clearer">[change]</a>
                    <p>Assess the performance of the average local business in your industry to help gauge your
                         expectations of how much businesses in your local market area make.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Use the <a href="javascript:gisp.dashboard.CompetitorAnalysis();">competitor map</a> to identify who 
                        your strongest local competitors and potential partners are.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="established answer collapsed hidden">
                    <h5>you are an established business</h5>
                    <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="clearer">[change]</a>
                    <p>
                        Comparing your revenue to the industry averages in your surrounding area will tell you 
                        whether you are outperforming your competition.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Use the <a href="javascript:gisp.dashboard.CompetitorAnalysis();">competitor map</a> to see who in
                         your area might be getting market-share revenue your company could have.  Once you have identified
                         your top competitors, think about what is allowing them to succeed, and then consider about 
                        how you might be able to outperform them.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Is your product or service faster, cheaper or better than the competition?
                          If the answer is "yes", make sure your competitors' customers know you are better to give
                         them a reason to buy from you.  Find the best places to <a href="javascript:gisp.dashboard.Advertise();">advertise</a>
                         or start a targeted <a href="javascript:gisp.dashboard.Advertise();">marketing campaign</a>.
                    </p>
                </div>


            </div>
            <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="considerationToggle fadeToggle" data-toggleText="More" data-toggleClass="collapsed">Less</a>
            <div class="section resources collapsable">


                 <h4>Resources</h4>
                <p>Post available jobs at <a href="http://hiring.monster.com" target="_blank">Monster</a>, <a href="http://www.careerbuilder.com/jobposter/"  target="_blank">CareerBuilder</a>, <a href="http://success.simplyhired.com" target="_blank">Simply Hired</a>, or <a href=https://ads.indeed.com" target="_blank">Indeed</a>.</p>
		        <p>Search resumes at <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a>, <a href="http://hiring.monster.com" target="_blank">Monster</a>, or <a href="http://www.careerbuilder.com/jobposter/"  target="_blank">CareerBuilder</a>.</p>
		        <p>Find temporary employees through <a href="http://www.manpower.com" target="_blank">Manpower</a>.</p>
	            <p>Augment salaries with a retention plan from <a href="http://retensa.com"  target="_blank">Retensa</a> and perks from <a href="http://betterworks.com"  target="_blank">BetterWorks</a>.</p>
                <p>Find salary data by occupation at <a href="http://salary.com"  target="_blank">Salary.com</a> or <a href="http://www.payscale.com/hr/solutions/salary-benchmarking"  target="_blank">PayScale</a>.</p>
		        <p>Enhance your employee benefits packages while saving your company money. Sign up for commuter benefit programs and flexible spending accounts through <a href="http://www.transitcenter.com/employers/"  target="_blank">TransitCheck</a>,
                <a href="https://www.flexdirect.adp.com/" target="_blank">FlexDirect</a>, or <a href="http://www.flex-plan.com/" target="_blank">Flex-Plan Services</a>.</p>






                @Html.Raw(ViewBag.Strings["Dashboard.Revenue.Resources"])
            </div>
            <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="resourcesToggle fadeToggle" data-toggleText="More" data-toggleClass="collapsed">Less</a>


        </div>
    </div>
</div>